whereas.text:
Whereas for every 5,000 to 10,000 compounds that enter the drug discovery pipeline, just 250
			 progress to preclinical development, and only one will become an approved
			 drug;

Whereas the aggregate research and development budget of the pharmaceutical industry has nearly
			 doubled from $68,000,000,000 in 2002 to $127,000,000,000 in 2010, there
			 has been little appreciable impact on the number of new drugs approved;

Whereas the lengthy process of biomedical innovation is becoming increasingly complex, expensive,
			 uncertain, and fraught with conflicting motivations and public-policy
			 implications;
